&lt;div style="color: red"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Experimental Nearshore&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
N.B. The nearshore data on this page is live and working but is being calibrated against local observations at the moment.&lt;p/&gt;

Covers Hells mouth and Aberdaron.

This forecast covers all the west facing breaks on the Mull of Kintyre from Glenbar south to Machrihanish including Westport, Middle Beach etc.&lt;p/&gt;

&lt;u&gt;Some local advice:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Swell height at beach is 1/3 of height at 62105, or height in metres at buoy = height in feet at beach. Needs direct west swell. Any kind of onshore/cross shore wind wrecks the wave as there is no shelter. Transit time of swell from buoy(62105) to beach is 12-15hrs. Minimum conditions are 7ft and 7secs with glassy sea, if worse than this, save yourself a drive!
